    "id": "slide8",
    "eyebrow": "Cultural Interactions",
    "num": "08",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">08</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Interactions</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Relations with Native American Tribes</h2><ul><li>Texicans had complex interactions including trade, conflict, and alliances</li><li>Shared cultural practices influenced by indigenous neighbors</li><li>Indigenous groups impacted Texican identity and regional dynamics</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans engaged with Native American tribes in multifaceted ways, shaping cultural exchange and political relationships that influenced the region's history. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican traders might exchange goods with Caddo tribes, adopting some indigenous customs in the process.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how these interactions could affect Texican cultural identity and security.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Avoid viewing Texican-indigenous relations as solely hostile; they were often cooperative and culturally influential.</p></div></div>",
