    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">12</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Summary</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Key Takeaways: Understanding 'Texican'</h2><ul><li>'Texican' denotes Mexican citizens in Texas during 1820-1836</li><li>Texicans had distinct cultural, legal, and social identities</li><li>Their role was central to early Texas history and complex political dynamics</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This summary consolidates the lesson’s core points, preparing learners to explore Texican settlement, lifestyle, and historical roles in subsequent sections. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Recognizing the Texican identity helps explain their unique perspectives during the Texas Revolution and interactions with other groups.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Reflect on how this understanding shapes your view of Texas history.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Do not overlook the importance of Texicans in early Texas narratives by focusing solely on Anglo settlers.</p></div></div>",
