    "eyebrow": "Cultural Influences",
    "num": "16",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">16</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Influences</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Mexican and Anglo Cultural Blending</h2><ul><li>Texicans spoke Spanish and English, often bilingually</li><li>Religious practices combined Catholicism with local traditions</li><li>Social customs reflected both Mexican and Anglo heritage</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican culture was a hybrid, merging Mexican legal and religious frameworks with Anglo social norms, producing a unique identity distinct from both parent cultures. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican festivals often included Catholic rituals alongside Anglo-style community gatherings.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify examples of cultural blending in Texican social life.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing Texican culture as monolithic or purely Mexican.</p></div></div>",
