    "num": "17",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">17</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Interactions</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Relations with Native American Tribes</h2><ul><li>Texicans engaged in trade and occasional conflict with tribes</li><li>Some alliances formed for mutual protection and economic benefit</li><li>Land competition often led to tensions and violence</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican interactions with Native Americans were complex, involving cooperation and conflict shaped by land use, trade, and cultural differences. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Trade of horses and goods occurred alongside sporadic skirmishes over territory.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze factors that influenced Texican-Native American relations.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Oversimplifying relations as purely hostile or friendly.</p></div></div>",
