    "num": "18",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">18</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Case Study</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Impact of Land Grant Policies on Texican Settlement</h2><ul><li>Land grants attracted diverse settlers under Mexican law</li><li>Settlers balanced Mexican citizenship requirements with Anglo cultural roots</li><li>Policy tensions contributed to eventual Texican resistance</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Land grant policies shaped who settled in Texas and how they identified culturally and politically, setting the stage for later conflicts. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Austin’s colony illustrates how land grants created a Texican population with mixed loyalties.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Evaluate how land grant policies influenced Texican political attitudes.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring the role of legal and cultural pressures in shaping settler identity.</p></div></div>",
