    "num": "20",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">20</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Analyzing Texican Settlement Patterns</h2><ul><li>Review maps of Texican land grants and settlements</li><li>Identify geographic and cultural factors influencing settlement</li><li>Consider Native American territories and interactions</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Practice interpreting historical settlement data to understand Texican community development and challenges. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Mapping Austin’s colony alongside Native lands reveals overlapping claims and potential conflicts.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Using provided maps, pinpoint key settlement areas and discuss their advantages and risks.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Neglecting the impact of indigenous presence on settlement choices.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide20\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;What is the origin of the term &#39;Texican&#39; as used during the Mexican Texas period?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;It referred to Anglo settlers only&quot;,&quot;It described Mexican residents of Texas blending Spanish and indigenous cultures&quot;,&quot;It was a term for Native American tribes in Texas&quot;,&quot;It was a nickname for Texas Rangers&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:1,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The term &#39;Texican&#39; historically referred to Mexican residents of Texas who embodied a cultural blend of Spanish colonial and indigenous influences during the Mexican Texas era.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain how the settlement patterns and lifestyle of the Texicans reflected their cultural background and interactions with Native American tribes.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;A strong answer will describe the Texicans&#39; settlement in Mexican Texas through land grants, their agricultural and ranching lifestyle, and how their culture was influenced by Spanish, Mexican, and indigenous traditions, including interactions that ranged from trade to conflict with Native American tribes.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Texicans settled primarily through Mexican land grant policies, establishing ranches and farms that reflected Spanish colonial traditions. Their lifestyle combined Mexican customs with indigenous influences, and they interacted with Native American tribes through both cooperation and conflict, shaping a unique cultural identity.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Texicans settled on land grants and lived farming and ranching lifestyles influenced by Spanish and indigenous cultures, interacting with Native Americans through trade and conflict&quot;,&quot;Their settlement patterns were shaped by Mexican policies, and their culture blended Spanish colonial and indigenous elements with active relations with Native tribes&quot;,&quot;They lived in communities influenced by Mexican and Native American cultures, settling land granted by Mexico and engaging with indigenous peoples&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
