    "eyebrow": "Texican Military Involvement",
    "num": "27",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">27</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Texican Military Involvement</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texicans in the Texas Revolution</h2><ul><li>Texicans formed militias to defend against Native American raids and Mexican forces</li><li>They played pivotal roles in battles such as Gonzales and the Alamo</li><li>Military involvement was both defensive and a push for political change</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans were active combatants in the Texas Revolution, organizing militias that engaged in key battles. Their military actions were motivated by defense needs and political aspirations for autonomy. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The Battle of Gonzales, where Texicans resisted Mexican troops, marked the revolution’s start and showcased Texican military resolve.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Explain how Texican military actions reflected both defense and political goals.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing Texican military efforts as purely offensive without recognizing defensive motivations.</p></div></div>",
