    "num": "30",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">30</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Texican Political Petition Example</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Analyzing a Texican Petition to Mexican Authorities</h2><ul><li>Petitions reveal Texican demands for rights and local governance</li><li>Language reflects respect for Mexican law but asserts Texican interests</li><li>Shows early political engagement before outright rebellion</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Examining a petition illustrates how Texicans sought to negotiate their position within Mexican Texas, balancing loyalty and autonomy. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A petition requesting exemption from certain Mexican laws to protect local customs and property rights.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify key demands and tone in the petition and discuss what it reveals about Texican political strategy.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Misinterpreting petitions as signs of weakness rather than strategic negotiation.</p></div></div>",
