    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">31</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Texican Militia Roster Example</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Examining a Texican Militia Roster from 1835</h2><ul><li>Roster lists names, ranks, and roles of Texican volunteers</li><li>Reflects community organization and military readiness</li><li>Provides insight into local leadership and participation</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">A militia roster offers concrete evidence of Texican military involvement and community mobilization during the revolution’s early stages. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Names on the roster include prominent Texican families, indicating social leadership in military efforts.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze the roster to infer social and military structures within Texican communities.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming militia rosters are complete or fully representative of all community members.</p></div></div>",
