    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">32</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Texican Battle Accounts</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Primary Accounts of Texican Battles</h2><ul><li>Eyewitness letters and reports describe Texican military actions</li><li>Accounts reveal motivations, challenges, and outcomes</li><li>Provide personal perspectives on the Texas Revolution</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Firsthand battle accounts give learners insight into Texican experiences and the realities of conflict during the revolution. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A letter from a Texican soldier describing the Battle of the Alamo highlights bravery and hardship.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Compare two battle accounts to identify differing perspectives and biases.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Taking all eyewitness accounts at face value without considering context or bias.</p></div></div>",
