    "num": "39",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">39</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Document Analysis Skills</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">How to Analyze Primary Sources</h2><ul><li>Identify the author, date, and purpose of the document</li><li>Consider the intended audience and possible biases</li><li>Examine language, tone, and key themes</li><li>Cross-check facts with other sources for reliability</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Analyzing primary sources requires understanding their context and critically evaluating their content to extract accurate historical information about the Texicans. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A letter from a Texican soldier may emphasize patriotism but omit dissenting opinions, indicating bias.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Choose a document and list potential biases or perspectives that might influence its content.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Taking all information at face value without questioning the source’s context or motive.</p></div></div>",
