    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">47</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice Checkpoint</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Evaluating a Texican Primary Source</h2><ul><li>Select a primary source excerpt provided</li><li>Identify author, date, and purpose</li><li>Analyze potential biases and language challenges</li><li>Summarize what the source reveals about Texican history</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This checkpoint reinforces document analysis skills by applying them to a new Texican source, preparing learners for independent research. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A newspaper announcement from 1835 reflects political tensions before the Texas Revolution.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write a brief analysis addressing the bullet points for your chosen source.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking context or failing to identify bias.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide47\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;What is the origin of the term &#39;Texican&#39; as used during the Mexican Texas period?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;It referred to Anglo settlers only&quot;,&quot;It described Mexican residents of Texas blending Spanish and indigenous cultures&quot;,&quot;It was a term for Native American tribes in Texas&quot;,&quot;It was a nickname for Texas Rangers&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:1,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The term &#39;Texican&#39; historically referred to Mexican residents of Texas who embodied a cultural blend of Spanish colonial and indigenous influences during the Mexican Texas era.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain how the settlement patterns and lifestyle of the Texicans reflected their cultural background and interactions with Native American tribes.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;A strong answer will describe the Texicans&#39; settlement in Mexican Texas through land grants, their agricultural and ranching lifestyle, and how their culture was influenced by Spanish, Mexican, and indigenous traditions, including interactions that ranged from trade to conflict with Native American tribes.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Texicans settled primarily through Mexican land grant policies, establishing ranches and farms that reflected Spanish colonial traditions. Their lifestyle combined Mexican customs with indigenous influences, and they interacted with Native American tribes through both cooperation and conflict, shaping a unique cultural identity.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Texicans settled on land grants and lived farming and ranching lifestyles influenced by Spanish and indigenous cultures, interacting with Native Americans through trade and conflict&quot;,&quot;Their settlement patterns were shaped by Mexican policies, and their culture blended Spanish colonial and indigenous elements with active relations with Native tribes&quot;,&quot;They lived in communities influenced by Mexican and Native American cultures, settling land granted by Mexico and engaging with indigenous peoples&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
