    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">48</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Summary and Transition</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Mastering Primary Source Analysis</h2><ul><li>Primary sources are essential for authentic Texican history</li><li>Critical analysis reveals context, bias, and meaning</li><li>Diverse document types enrich understanding</li><li>Awareness of limitations guides responsible interpretation</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This slide summarizes key takeaways from the primary source section and prepares learners to apply these skills in broader historical contexts. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Combining a land grant with a settler’s letter provides a fuller picture of Texican settlement challenges.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Consider how you will use primary sources in your own study of Texican history.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Neglecting to question sources or integrate multiple perspectives.</p></div></div>",
