    "eyebrow": "Review and Integration",
    "num": "54",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">54</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Review and Integration</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Interactive Quiz: Texican Identity and History</h2><ul><li>Test your knowledge on Texican origins, culture, and historical roles.</li><li>Identify key terms, figures, and events discussed in the course.</li><li>Use quiz feedback to clarify any misconceptions.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">An interactive quiz consolidates learning by prompting recall and application of key concepts about Texicans and their historical context. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Sample question: What indigenous word is the origin of 'Texas'? Answer: 'táysha' meaning 'friends' or 'allies.'</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Complete the quiz and review explanations for each answer.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Guessing without reviewing course material, leading to missed learning opportunities.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide54\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;What is the origin of the term &#39;Texican&#39; as used during the Mexican Texas period?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;It referred to Anglo settlers only&quot;,&quot;It described Mexican residents of Texas blending Spanish and indigenous cultures&quot;,&quot;It was a term for Native American tribes in Texas&quot;,&quot;It was a nickname for Texas Rangers&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:1,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The term &#39;Texican&#39; historically referred to Mexican residents of Texas who embodied a cultural blend of Spanish colonial and indigenous influences during the Mexican Texas era.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain how the settlement patterns and lifestyle of the Texicans reflected their cultural background and interactions with Native American tribes.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;A strong answer will describe the Texicans&#39; settlement in Mexican Texas through land grants, their agricultural and ranching lifestyle, and how their culture was influenced by Spanish, Mexican, and indigenous traditions, including interactions that ranged from trade to conflict with Native American tribes.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Texicans settled primarily through Mexican land grant policies, establishing ranches and farms that reflected Spanish colonial traditions. Their lifestyle combined Mexican customs with indigenous influences, and they interacted with Native American tribes through both cooperation and conflict, shaping a unique cultural identity.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Texicans settled on land grants and lived farming and ranching lifestyles influenced by Spanish and indigenous cultures, interacting with Native Americans through trade and conflict&quot;,&quot;Their settlement patterns were shaped by Mexican policies, and their culture blended Spanish colonial and indigenous elements with active relations with Native tribes&quot;,&quot;They lived in communities influenced by Mexican and Native American cultures, settling land granted by Mexico and engaging with indigenous peoples&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
