    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">58</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Review and Integration</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Applying Knowledge: Analyzing a Primary Source Excerpt</h2><ul><li>Examine a brief excerpt from a Texican-era document.</li><li>Identify references to indigenous influence or cultural blending.</li><li>Interpret the document's significance in historical context.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Analyzing primary sources reinforces learners' ability to connect course concepts with historical evidence. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A letter mentioning alliances with native groups illustrates political and social relationships.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Read the excerpt and answer guided questions about its content and implications.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring the cultural context or reading the document with present-day assumptions.</p></div></div>",
