    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">59</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Review and Integration</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Transfer Practice: Connecting Texican History to Modern Texas</h2><ul><li>Consider how Texican cultural blending influences modern Texan identity.</li><li>Identify contemporary examples of indigenous and Mexican heritage in Texas.</li><li>Reflect on the importance of historical awareness in regional identity.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This slide encourages learners to apply historical knowledge to understand ongoing cultural influences in modern Texas. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Modern Texas festivals celebrating Mexican and indigenous heritage reflect enduring Texican cultural roots.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> List ways Texican history is visible in today's Texas culture and society.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing history as disconnected from present-day identity and culture.</p></div></div>",
